.TH "kvm_mmu_clear_dirty_pt_masked" 9 "kvm_mmu_clear_dirty_pt_masked" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kvm_mmu_clear_dirty_pt_masked \- clear MMU D-bit for PT level pages, or write protect the page if the D-bit isn't supported.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" kvm_mmu_clear_dirty_pt_masked
.BI "(struct kvm *kvm "  ","
.BI "struct kvm_memory_slot *slot "  ","
.BI "gfn_t gfn_offset "  ","
.BI "unsigned long mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kvm" 12
kvm instance
.IP "slot" 12
slot to clear D-bit
.IP "gfn_offset" 12
start of the BITS_PER_LONG pages we care about
.IP "mask" 12
indicates which pages we should clear D-bit
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Used for PML to re-log the dirty GPAs after userspace querying dirty_bitmap.
